:INFO
The Friends-to-Lovers Novel That Made Me Cry on a Train
People We Meet on Vacation alternates between the present and annual vacation \
chapters spread over ten years. The structure is what makes it work: you see the \
friendship and the slow shift underneath it before either character names what \
is happening. Emily Henry is very good at the specific emotional cost of wanting \
something you are afraid to want. By the time I reached the final chapters I was \
crying on a commuter train and did not particularly mind.

:NOTE
The friendship is more convincing than the romance. That is a compliment.

:QUOTE [subtitle:Emily Henry, quotetype:PLAIN]
Every year was a year with Alex in it. Those were the best years I had.

:JOURNEY
